radiographic_examinations.findings: Enlarged thyroid gland at neonatal screening, elevated TSH (58 mU/liter), and later persistent high serum TSH level (151 mU/liter)
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Two years later, after 1 month of L-T4 withdrawal, the serum TSH rose to 5.3 mU/liter, while the serum free T4 concentration remained within normal range.
